INSURECORP HEALTH PROTECT POLICY
Simplified Policy Document for AI Claims Intelligence & Fraud Detection Project

1. Policy Overview

Policy Type: Individual / Family Health Insurance

Policy Period: 1 Year

Coverage: Hospitalization & Surgery

Claim Mode: Cashless (Network) / Reimbursement (Non-Network)

2. Eligibility Criteria

Minimum Entry Age: 18 years

Maximum Entry Age: 65 years

Dependent Children Covered up to 25 years

Policy must be active on date of admission

3. In-Patient Hospitalization Coverage

Hospitalization must exceed 24 consecutive hours

Treatment must be medically necessary

Hospital must be registered

Covered: Room Rent, ICU, Surgery Charges, Doctor Fees, Medicines, Diagnostics

4. Waiting Period Rules

Initial Waiting Period: 30 days from policy start (except accidents)

Specific Surgeries Waiting Period: 1 year

Pre-existing Disease Waiting Period: 2 years

5. Sum Insured & Limits

Sum Insured Range: ■2,00,000 – ■10,00,000

Maximum Claim Amount = Sum Insured

Room Rent Limit: 1% of Sum Insured per day

ICU Limit: 2% of Sum Insured per day

Excess charges result in proportionate deductions

6. Hospital Network Rules

Cashless allowed only at Network Hospitals

Non-network hospitals eligible for reimbursement only

Blacklisted hospitals result in claim rejection

7. Claim Validation Conditions

Policy active at time of admission

Claim filed within 30 days of discharge

Diagnosis must match treatment

Itemized bills required

Medical necessity required

8. Exclusions

Cosmetic or elective procedures

OPD consultations

Self-inflicted injuries

Experimental treatments

Treatment during waiting period

Duplicate or fabricated claims

9. Fraud Risk Indicators

Claim exceeds Sum Insured significantly

Repeated claims within 60 days

Hospital used excessively for high-value claims

Diagnosis-treatment mismatch

Waiting period violation

Inflated room rent charges

Blacklisted hospital usage

10. Fraud Risk Scoring Model (For AI Agent Use)

Waiting Period Violation: +0.25 Risk Weight

Claim > Sum Insured: +0.30 Risk Weight

Non-Network Hospital: +0.10 Risk Weight

Blacklisted Hospital: +0.40 Risk Weight

Frequent Claims: +0.20 Risk Weight

Diagnosis Mismatch: +0.25 Risk Weight

Risk Levels: Low (0-0.4), Medium (0.4-0.7), High (0.7-1.0)

11. Network Hospital List (Sample)

CityCare Medical Center

Global Health Hospital

MetroLife Surgical Center

12. Blacklisted Hospitals (Sample)

Sunrise Care Center

QuickClaim Health Hub

This simplified policy document is created specifically for the Enterprise Insurance Claims
Intelligence & Fraud Detection Copilot Project. It is intended for academic and system design
purposes only.
